In the TUGraz lecture "Introduction to Data Science and Artificial Intelligence (IDSA)", different definitions of intelligence have been discussed. According to different definitions, something or someone would be called intelligent if it thinks humanly, acts humanly, thinks rationally, acts rationally; or if it is able to adapt behaviour to a changing environment in order to achieve its goals.
I have this information from here. But, I'm not sure I completely understand.
